      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is the `calculate_entropy` function implemented to specifically handle frequency distributions with 4-decimal precision to avoid floating-point issues.\n\n```python\nimport math\n\ndef calculate_entropy(ips):\n    if not ips:\n        return 0.0\n    total = len(ips)\n    counts = {}\n    for ip in ips:\n        counts[ip] = counts.get(ip, 0) + 1\n    \n    entropy = 0.0\n    for count in counts.values():\n        probability = count / total\n        if probability > 0:\n            entropy -= probability * math.log2(probability)\n    return round(entropy, 4)\n```\n\nThis solution aggregates the IP addresses to count unique occurrences, calculates the probability for each, and applies the Shannon entropy formula with explicit rounding to match your assertions.",
